c static class TestApplication {\n\n        @Bean\n        ConfigurationCustomizer configurationCustomizer() {\n            return configuration -> {\n                configuration.setMapUnderscoreToCamelCase(true);\n                configuration.setCallSettersOnNulls(true);\n            };\n        }\n\n        @Bean\n        MybatisPlusPropertiesCustomizer mybatisPlusPropertiesCustomizer() {\n            return properties -> properties.setExecutorType(ExecutorType.REUSE);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Mapper\n    public interface AccountMapper extends BaseMapper<Account> {\n    }\n\n    @TableName(\"account\")\n    public static class Account {\n        @TableId(type = IdType.INPUT)\n        private Long id;\n        private String userName;\n        private Integer age;\n\n        public Long getId() {\n            return id;\n        }\n\n        public void setId(Long id) {\n            this.id = id;\n        }\n\n        public String getUserName() {\n            return userName;\n        }\n\n        public void setUserName(String userName) {\n            this.userName = userName;\n        }\n\n        public Integer getAge() {\n            return age;\n        }\n\n        public void setAge(Integer age) {\n            this.age = age;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingDdl implements IDdl {\n        private final AtomicInteger invocations = new AtomicInteger();\n        private final AtomicReference<List<String>> observedSqlFiles = new AtomicReference<>(List.of());\n\n        @Override\n        public void runScript(java.util.function.Consumer<DataSource> consumer) {\n            invocations.incrementAndGet();\n            observedSqlFiles.set(getSqlFiles());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public List<String> getSqlFiles() {\n            return List.of(\"schema/account.sql\", \"schema/audit.sql\");\n        }\n\n        int invocations() {\n            return invocations.get();\n        }\n\n        List<String> observedSqlFiles() {\n            return observedSqlFiles.get();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating SpringBootVFS testing**\n\nI’m considering the need for `SpringBootVFS` test lists and whether resources are available in a native image. Class resources might not be present under native conditions, and resolving `classpath*:.../**/*.class` might not work without resources metadata. Tests should run natively with this metadata, but it could be a challenge. There’s a concern about resource inclusion potentially bloating the application, especially without current metadata. I’m also thinking about the implications for MyBatis and ensuring high coverage for dynamic access in tests.\n\n**Considering MyBatisPlusAutoConfiguration**\n\nI need to review MyBatisPlusAutoConfiguration, focusing on aspects like Scanner, properties, customizers, and SafetyEncryptProcessor. It's crucial to ensure there's enough coverage without direct reflection. I wonder if Spring Boot's auto-configuration loads EnvironmentPostProcessor automatically when using SpringApplication, especially with our safety tests. Also, I need to manage imports for AES and various MyBatisPlus components.\n\nThere could be a concern about H2 version compatibility, particularly since the starter references Spring Boot 2.5.3. If the test project has its platform, we'll need to set specific versions, like `com.h2database:h2:2.1.214`. I might need to adjust the maximum pool size and connection timeout settings as well. Lastly, I notice some potential issues with annotations in MyBatis-Plus and configuration in my test setup.\n\n**Implementing MapperScan**\n\nI need to use `@MapperScan(basePackageClasses = AccountMapper.class)` in the configuration. This annotation helps specify the package for scanning MyBatis mappers, ensuring I include all necessary mappers related to account functions. It's a straightforward way to streamline mapper management in my project. By doing this, I can avoid potentia